A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of William G. Fallin; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of William G. Fallin on January 4, 2025; and
4 WHEREAS, William G. Fallin was born on September 9, 1932, in Thomas County, Georgia,
5 a beloved son of Brady and Ernestine Fallin; and
6 WHEREAS, he served as a guardian of this nation's freedom and liberty with the United
7 States Army, valiantly and courageously protecting his fellow Americans during the Korean
8 War; and
9 WHEREAS, a man of deep and abiding faith, William G. Fallin was an active member of
10 First Baptist Church, where he served as a Deacon, Sunday School Teacher, choir member,
11 and co-chair of two renovation projects; and
12 WHEREAS, he was united in love and marriage to his wife of 67 years, Barbara, and was
13 blessed with three children, Leah, Laura, and William; six wonderful grandchildren, Ernest,
